==English==

===Verb===
'''scrounge'''
# To take advantage of someone's [[good will]]
# To take from someone to the latter's detriment, to [[cadge]]
# To live off someone else's good will, like a lazy old slacker
# To cunningly steal (something minor)
# To intend to take without any thoughts for giving anything back
# To hunt for [[freebie]]s
# To attempt to suck free stuff away from goodminded people, without any guilt or feelings towards them, like a leech.
#:''As long as he's got someone who'll let him scrounge off them, he'll never settle down and get a full-time job''
 
